1 byte = 8 bits 

Show what the following decimal values look like in 
8-bit binary, 3-digit octal, and 2-digit hexadecimal:

int = 4 bytes = 32 bits 
0000 ... 0001
1111 ... 1111

1
binary: 0000 0001
octal:  001
hexa:   0x01

8
binary: 0000 1000
octal:  010
hexa:   0x08

10

15

16

100
binary: 0110 0100
octal:  144
hexa:   0x64

127
binary: 0111 1111
octal:  177
hexa:   0x7F

1000 << 3

200
